rsa.internal.word.description: This is used by the Word Parsing technology to capture the first 5 character of every word in an unparsed log

rsa.investigations.analysis_file.description: This is used to capture all indicators used in a File Analysis. This key should be used to capture an analysis of a file

rsa.investigations.analysis_service.description: This is used to capture all indicators used in a Service Analysis. This key should be used to capture an analysis of a service

rsa.investigations.analysis_session.description: This is used to capture all indicators used for a Session Analysis. This key should be used to capture an analysis of a session

rsa.investigations.boc.description: This is used to capture behaviour of compromise

rsa.investigations.ec_activity.description: This key captures the particular event activity(Ex:Logoff)

rsa.investigations.ec_outcome.description: This key captures the outcome of a particular Event(Ex:Success)

rsa.investigations.ec_subject.description: This key captures the Subject of a particular Event(Ex:User)

rsa.investigations.ec_theme.description: This key captures the Theme of a particular Event(Ex:Authentication)

rsa.investigations.eoc.description: This is used to capture Enablers of Compromise

rsa.investigations.event_cat.description: This key captures the Event category number

rsa.investigations.event_cat_name.description: This key captures the event category name corresponding to the event cat code

rsa.investigations.event_vcat.description: This is a vendor supplied category. This should be used in situations where the vendor has adopted their own event_category taxonomy.

rsa.investigations.inv_category.description: This used to capture investigation category

rsa.investigations.inv_context.description: This used to capture investigation context

rsa.investigations.ioc.description: This is key capture indicator of compromise

rsa.misc.OS.description: This key captures the Name of the Operating System

rsa.misc.agent_id.description: This key is used to capture agent id

rsa.misc.alert_id.description: Deprecated, New Hunting Model (inv.*, ioc, boc, eoc, analysis.*)

rsa.misc.autorun_type.description: This is used to capture Auto Run type

rsa.misc.category.description: This key is used to capture the category of an event given by the vendor in the session

rsa.misc.change_attrib.description: This key is used to capture the name of the attribute thats changing in a session

rsa.misc.change_new.description: This key is used to capture the new values of the attribute thats changing in a session

rsa.misc.change_old.description: This key is used to capture the old value of the attribute thats changing in a session

rsa.misc.checksum.description: This key is used to capture the checksum or hash of the entity such as a file or process. Checksum should be used over checksum.src or checksum.dst when it is unclear whether the entity is a source or target of an action.

rsa.misc.checksum_dst.description: This key is used to capture the checksum or hash of the the target entity such as a process or file.

rsa.misc.checksum_src.description: This key is used to capture the checksum or hash of the source entity such as a file or process.

rsa.misc.client.description: This key is used to capture only the name of the client application requesting resources of the server. See the user.agent meta key for capture of the specific user agent identifier or browser identification string.

rsa.misc.comments.description: Comment information provided in the log message

rsa.misc.comp_version.description: This key captures the Version level of a sub-component of a product.

rsa.misc.connection_id.description: This key captures the Connection ID

rsa.misc.content.description: This key captures the content type from protocol headers

rsa.misc.content_type.description: This key is used to capture Content Type only.

rsa.misc.content_version.description: This key captures Version level of a signature or database content.

rsa.misc.context.description: This key captures Information which adds additional context to the event.

rsa.misc.context_subject.description: This key is to be used in an audit context where the subject is the object being identified

rsa.misc.cpu.description: This key is the CPU time used in the execution of the event being recorded.

rsa.misc.cve.description: This key captures CVE (Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures) - an identifier for known information security vulnerabilities.

rsa.misc.device_name.description: This is used to capture name of the Device associated with the node Like: a physical disk, printer, etc

rsa.misc.disposition.description: This key captures the The end state of an action.

rsa.misc.doc_number.description: This key captures File Identification number

rsa.misc.error.description: This key captures All non successful Error codes or responses

rsa.misc.event_computer.description: This key is a windows only concept, where this key is used to capture fully qualified domain name in a windows log.

rsa.misc.event_desc.description: This key is used to capture a description of an event available directly or inferred

rsa.misc.event_log.description: This key captures the Name of the event log

rsa.misc.event_source.description: This key captures Source of the event thats not a hostname

rsa.misc.event_state.description: This key captures the current state of the object/item referenced within the event. Describing an on-going event.

rsa.misc.event_type.description: This key captures the event category type as specified by the event source.

rsa.misc.event_user.description: This key is a windows only concept, where this key is used to capture combination of domain name and username in a windows log.

rsa.misc.expected_val.description: This key captures the Value expected (from the perspective of the device generating the log).

rsa.misc.fcatnum.description: This key captures Filter Category Number. Legacy Usage

rsa.misc.filter.description: This key captures Filter used to reduce result set

rsa.misc.found.description: This is used to capture the results of regex match

rsa.misc.fresult.description: This key captures the Filter Result

rsa.misc.group.description: This key captures the Group Name value

rsa.misc.group_id.description: This key captures Group ID Number (related to the group name)

rsa.misc.group_object.description: This key captures a collection/grouping of entities. Specific usage

rsa.misc.hardware_id.description: This key is used to capture unique identifier for a device or system (NOT a Mac address)

rsa.misc.job_num.description: This key captures the Job Number

rsa.misc.language.description: This is used to capture list of languages the client support and what it prefers

rsa.misc.library.description: This key is used to capture library information in mainframe devices

rsa.misc.lifetime.description: This key is used to capture the session lifetime in seconds.

rsa.misc.link.description: This key is used to link the sessions together. This key should never be used to parse Meta data from a session (Logs/Packets) Directly, this is a Reserved key in NetWitness

rsa.misc.listnum.description: This key is used to capture listname or listnumber, primarily for collecting access-list

rsa.misc.log_session_id.description: This key is used to capture a sessionid from the session directly

rsa.misc.log_session_id1.description: This key is used to capture a Linked (Related) Session ID from the session directly

rsa.misc.mail_id.description: This key is used to capture the mailbox id/name

rsa.misc.match.description: This key is for regex match name from search.ini

rsa.misc.message_body.description: This key captures the The contents of the message body.

rsa.misc.node.description: Common use case is the node name within a cluster. The cluster name is reflected by the host name.

rsa.misc.obj_name.description: This is used to capture name of object

rsa.misc.obj_type.description: This is used to capture type of object

rsa.misc.observed_val.description: This key captures the Value observed (from the perspective of the device generating the log).

rsa.misc.operation_id.description: An alert number or operation number. The values should be unique and non-repeating.

rsa.misc.param.description: This key is the parameters passed as part of a command or application, etc.

rsa.misc.param_dst.description: This key captures the command line/launch argument of the target process or file

rsa.misc.parent_node.description: This key captures the Parent Node Name. Must be related to node variable.

rsa.misc.payload_dst.description: This key is used to capture destination payload

rsa.misc.payload_src.description: This key is used to capture source payload

rsa.misc.policy_id.description: This key is used to capture the Policy ID only, this should be a numeric value, use policy.name otherwise

rsa.misc.policy_name.description: This key is used to capture the Policy Name only.

rsa.misc.policy_value.description: This key captures the contents of the policy. This contains details about the policy

rsa.misc.pool_id.description: This key captures the identifier (typically numeric field) of a resource pool

rsa.misc.pool_name.description: This key captures the name of a resource pool

rsa.misc.port_name.description: This key is used for Physical or logical port connection but does NOT include a network port. (Example: Printer port name).

rsa.misc.process_id_val.description: This key is a failure key for Process ID when it is not an integer value

rsa.misc.reference_id.description: This key is used to capture an event id from the session directly

rsa.misc.reference_id1.description: This key is for Linked ID to be used as an addition to "reference.id"

rsa.misc.reference_id2.description: This key is for the 2nd Linked ID. Can be either linked to "reference.id" or "reference.id1" value but should not be used unless the other two variables are in play.

rsa.misc.result.description: This key is used to capture the outcome/result string value of an action in a session.

rsa.misc.result_code.description: This key is used to capture the outcome/result numeric value of an action in a session

rsa.misc.risk.description: This key captures the non-numeric risk value

rsa.misc.risk_info.description: Deprecated, use New Hunting Model (inv.*, ioc, boc, eoc, analysis.*)

rsa.misc.risk_num.description: This key captures a Numeric Risk value

rsa.misc.risk_num_comm.description: This key captures Risk Number Community

rsa.misc.risk_num_next.description: This key captures Risk Number NextGen

rsa.misc.risk_num_sand.description: This key captures Risk Number SandBox

rsa.misc.risk_num_static.description: This key captures Risk Number Static

rsa.misc.risk_suspicious.description: Deprecated, use New Hunting Model (inv.*, ioc, boc, eoc, analysis.*)

rsa.misc.risk_warning.description: Deprecated, use New Hunting Model (inv.*, ioc, boc, eoc, analysis.*)

rsa.misc.rule.description: This key captures the Rule number

rsa.misc.rule_group.description: This key captures the Rule group name

rsa.misc.rule_name.description: This key captures the Rule Name

rsa.misc.rule_template.description: A default set of parameters which are overlayed onto a rule (or rulename) which efffectively constitutes a template

rsa.misc.rule_uid.description: This key is the Unique Identifier for a rule.

rsa.misc.search_text.description: This key captures the Search Text used

rsa.misc.sensor.description: This key captures Name of the sensor. Typically used in IDS/IPS based devices

rsa.misc.serial_number.description: This key is the Serial number associated with a physical asset.

rsa.misc.severity.description: This key is used to capture the severity given the session

rsa.misc.sig_id.description: This key captures IDS/IPS Int Signature ID

rsa.misc.sig_id1.description: This key captures IDS/IPS Int Signature ID. This must be linked to the sig.id

rsa.misc.sig_id_str.description: This key captures a string object of the sigid variable.

rsa.misc.sig_name.description: This key is used to capture the Signature Name only.

rsa.misc.sql.description: This key captures the SQL query

rsa.misc.streams.description: This key captures number of streams in session

rsa.misc.tcp_flags.description: This key is captures the TCP flags set in any packet of session

rsa.misc.terminal.description: This key captures the Terminal Names only

rsa.misc.tos.description: This key describes the type of service

rsa.misc.trigger_desc.description: This key captures the Description of the trigger or threshold condition.

rsa.misc.trigger_val.description: This key captures the Value of the trigger or threshold condition.

rsa.misc.version.description: This key captures Version of the application or OS which is generating the event.

rsa.misc.virusname.description: This key captures the name of the virus

rsa.misc.vsys.description: This key captures Virtual System Name

rsa.misc.vuln_ref.description: This key captures the Vulnerability Reference details

rsa.network.alias_host.description: This key should be used when the source or destination context of a hostname is not clear.Also it captures the Device Hostname. Any Hostname that isnt ad.computer.

rsa.network.dinterface.description: This key should only be used when its a Destination Interface

rsa.network.dmask.description: This key is used for Destionation Device network mask

rsa.network.eth_type.description: This key is used to capture Ethernet Type, Used for Layer 3 Protocols Only

rsa.network.gateway.description: This key is used to capture the IP Address of the gateway

rsa.network.host_dst.description: This key should only be used when its a Destination Hostname

rsa.network.host_orig.description: This is used to capture the original hostname in case of a Forwarding Agent or a Proxy in between.

rsa.network.icmp_code.description: This key is used to capture the ICMP code only

rsa.network.icmp_type.description: This key is used to capture the ICMP type only

rsa.network.interface.description: This key should be used when the source or destination context of an interface is not clear

rsa.network.ip_proto.description: This key should be used to capture the Protocol number, all the protocol nubers are converted into string in UI

rsa.network.mask.description: This key is used to capture the device network IPmask.

rsa.network.netname.description: This key is used to capture the network name associated with an IP range. This is configured by the end user.

rsa.network.network_port.description: Deprecated, use port. NOTE: There is a type discrepancy as currently used, TM: Int32, INDEX: UInt64 (why neither chose the correct UInt16?!)

rsa.network.network_service.description: This is used to capture layer 7 protocols/service names

rsa.network.port.description: This key should only be used to capture a Network Port when the directionality is not clear

rsa.network.protocol_detail.description: This key should be used to capture additional protocol information

rsa.network.rpayload.description: This key is used to capture the total number of payload bytes seen in the retransmitted packets.

rsa.network.sinterface.description: This key should only be used when its a Source Interface

rsa.network.smask.description: This key is used for capturing source Network Mask

rsa.network.vlan.description: This key should only be used to capture the ID of the Virtual LAN

rsa.network.vlan_name.description: This key should only be used to capture the name of the Virtual LAN

rsa.network.zone.description: This key should be used when the source or destination context of a Zone is not clear

rsa.network.zone_dst.description: This key should only be used when its a Destination Zone.

rsa.network.zone_src.description: This key should only be used when its a Source Zone.

rsa.physical.org_dst.description: This is used to capture the destination organization based on the GEOPIP Maxmind database.

rsa.physical.org_src.description: This is used to capture the source organization based on the GEOPIP Maxmind database.

rsa.storage.disk_volume.description: A unique name assigned to logical units (volumes) within a physical disk

rsa.storage.lun.description: Logical Unit Number.This key is a very useful concept in Storage.

rsa.storage.pwwn.description: This uniquely identifies a port on a HBA.

rsa.threat.alert.description: This key is used to capture name of the alert

rsa.threat.threat_category.description: This key captures Threat Name/Threat Category/Categorization of alert

rsa.threat.threat_desc.description: This key is used to capture the threat description from the session directly or inferred

rsa.threat.threat_source.description: This key is used to capture source of the threat

rsa.time.duration_str.description: A text string version of the duration

rsa.time.duration_time.description: This key is used to capture the normalized duration/lifetime in seconds.

rsa.time.effective_time.description: This key is the effective time referenced by an individual event in a Standard Timestamp format

rsa.time.endtime.description: This key is used to capture the End time mentioned in a session in a standard form

rsa.time.event_queue_time.description: This key is the Time that the event was queued.

rsa.time.event_time.description: This key is used to capture the time mentioned in a raw session that represents the actual time an event occured in a standard normalized form

rsa.time.event_time_str.description: This key is used to capture the incomplete time mentioned in a session as a string

rsa.time.expire_time.description: This key is the timestamp that explicitly refers to an expiration.

rsa.time.expire_time_str.description: This key is used to capture incomplete timestamp that explicitly refers to an expiration.

rsa.time.recorded_time.description: The event time as recorded by the system the event is collected from. The usage scenario is a multi-tier application where the management layer of the system records it's own timestamp at the time of collection from its child nodes. Must be in timestamp format.

rsa.time.stamp.description: Deprecated key defined only in table map.

rsa.time.starttime.description: This key is used to capture the Start time mentioned in a session in a standard form

rsa.time.timezone.description: This key is used to capture the timezone of the Event Time

rsa.web.reputation_num.description: Reputation Number of an entity. Typically used for Web Domains

rsa.web.web_cookie.description: This key is used to capture the Web cookies specifically.

rsa.web.web_ref_page.description: This key captures Web referer's page information

rsa.web.web_ref_query.description: This key captures Web referer's query portion of the URL

rsa.wireless.access_point.description: This key is used to capture the access point name.

rsa.wireless.wlan_channel.description: This is used to capture the channel names

rsa.wireless.wlan_name.description: This key captures either WLAN number/name

rsa.wireless.wlan_ssid.description: This key is used to capture the ssid of a Wireless Session
